2. What information do we collect from you?
Source:
The information collected includes the following data:
Your name, email address, or other contact information communicated to us.
Any Personal Data provided in and through communication channels available in our Services.
If you have subscribed to our communications, your content preferences, language, and contact information.
If you participate in our surveys or other research, any comments, feedback, responses, or other information you provide to us.
Additional information when using our BitLife services, such as Appsflyer ID and unique account identifiers automatically created upon application installation.
Your device and browser data, usage data, and automatically collected data.
3. How do we use your Personal Data?
We use your Personal Data to:
Provide you with the Services you have requested.
Improve and develop our Services.
Predict user trends and make recommendations.
Customize our Services based on your preferences.
4. Who we share your information with
Your Personal Data will be transferred or disclosed to third parties, such as:
Other companies in the Stillfront Group.
Service providers who help us develop and operate our Services.
Third-party services when you link or connect your accounts with our Services.
Competent courts of law or other government authorities when required by law.
5. Appropriate Safeguards to countries outside the EU/EEA-area
In connection with the processing activities described in this Privacy Policy, we share information outside of the European Union (EU) and the European Economic Area (EEA). Where the Company transfers Personal Data outside the EU/EEA, appropriate safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses will be put in place to protect your Personal Data during the transfer.
6. How long do we keep hold of your information?
We will retain your information only for as long as is necessary for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy, based on the following criteria:
Ongoing relationship with you
Legal obligations
Advisable in light of our legal position
7. Security
We have implemented appropriate technical, physical, and organisational measures to protect your Personal Data against unauthorised or accidental destruction, alteration, disclosure, or loss.
8. Your rights under the GDPR and applicable Data Protection Law
You have the right to:
Access your data
Object to certain processing
Rectify inaccuracies
Erasure of data
Restrict processing
Withdraw consent
Data portability
Complain to the supervisory authority
9. US Residents
If you are based in the United States, please refer to the US-specific section of this policy for more information on your rights.
10. Changes to the terms of this Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy from time to time due to changes in our operations, new partners, or legal obligations.
